# File Copy Program with Threads

This C program demonstrates file copying using two threads, one for reading from the source file, and another for writing to the destination file. The program uses semaphores to synchronize access to shared resources which contains a buffer with limited size and an integer for specifying end of source file. unit of producer process is "line" limited to 1024 b . each time consumer waits for producer to read unit and put it in buffer . 

## Instructions to Run

### Prerequisites

Make sure you have a C compiler installed on your system. If not, you can install one using your system's package manager.

### Compilation

Compile the program using Makefiel with the following command:

```bash
make
./copy <srcfile> <dstfile>
